## ⚡ Quick Start (2 minutes)

**See Nova fix 10 bugs automatically:**

```bash
# One-line quickstart - just paste and run!
curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/joinnova-ci/nova-ci-rescue/main/quickstart.sh | bash
```

**What happens:**

1. 🔑 Enter your OpenAI API key (if not already set)
2. 📦 Nova installs automatically via pip
3. 🧪 Creates a calculator demo with 10 broken mathematical functions
4. ❌ Shows all 10 tests failing → 🤖 Nova analyzes and fixes each bug → ✅ All tests pass
5. 🎉 **Result:** 10 different bug types fixed automatically in 2-3 minutes

**Requirements:** Python 3.8+, OpenAI API key

### Ignore virtualenvs and build artifacts (recommended)

Nova now respects a built‑in ignore list so it won’t scan files inside common virtualenv and dependency folders (e.g., `.venv`, `venv`, `site-packages`, `node_modules`, caches). You can further customize this with:

- .novaignore file at the repo root (glob patterns supported)
- `NOVA_IGNORE_PATHS` env var (comma or newline separated patterns)

Examples:

```bash
echo -e ".venv\nnode_modules\n**/generated/**" > .novaignore
export NOVA_IGNORE_PATHS=".env,.tox,.pytest_cache,dist,build"
```

