## 📊 The Problem: $61B Annual Tax on Velocity

**Every failed CI run costs ~$60 in lost developer time:**

- **~18% of CI runs fail** — Industry average is 82% success vs 90% for elite teams [Source: CircleCI 2024 State of Software Delivery](https://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20240416151568/en/)
- **620M developer hours wasted annually** — 26% of dev time debugging failures [Source: Cambridge University/Undo Study](https://devops.com/report-debugging-efforts-cost-companies-61b-annually/)
- **56% of engineers blocked by CI failures** [Source: Cambridge Study via DevOps.com](https://devops.com/report-debugging-efforts-cost-companies-61b-annually/)

**The trust gap:** 84% of developers use AI tools, only 29% trust the outputs

[Source: Stack Overflow 2025 Survey](https://survey.stackoverflow.co/2025)

---

## 🚀 Our Solution: The Critic Loop

`Red PR → Nova reproduces → patches → verifies → opens green PR`

**What makes Nova different:**

- **Authority from tests, not prompts** — Your CI is the oracle
- **Minimal diffs you can review** — Targets small patches (typically under ~50 lines across a few files)
- **Side-branch safety** — Never touches main
- **Full audit trail** — Every patch includes rationale

**The 4-step loop:** Plan → Generate → Patch → **Critic** _(re-runs CI, iterates if needed)_

